race.comment: IMPORT (5) missed in a blanket finish as a 30-1 pop on debut but showed it was no fluke with a solid effort last start over 1300m here. Faithfull rides now, he maps well and the slight rise in trip is ideal. Can get the job done this time around. PUISSANCE PLAYBOY (2) is knocking on the door of a maiden win and looks better suited dropping back to this course and distance. The wide draw is a query, but he has the pace to offset the tricky draw. Can pick up his maiden win with a touch of luck. DESERT MADAME (10) flew home first-up over 1300m to finish 1L off the winner in a strong return. She'll be fitter for that effort, she draws better today and the rise in trip suits. Can make her presence felt. WRITTEN SIN (9) wasn't beaten far in that same race that DESERT MADAME comes through and is worth including. REIGN IN THE CASH (1) is better than he showed last start and can bounce back dropping in distance.
